      "lesson title": "False Confidence in AI Predictions",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "In this lesson, you will explore how artificial intelligence systems can generate predictions that appear highly confident but are fundamentally flawed or misleading. We will examine real-world scenarios where organisations have relied too heavily on AI-generated insights, leading to poor decision-making and serious operational consequences. You will learn to recognise the warning signs of overconfident AI outputs, including how numerical scores and probability figures can create a false sense of certainty. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of why critical thinking and human oversight remain essential when working alongside AI tools. This knowledge will help you make safer, more informed decisions in your own professional context.",
