          "slidetitle": "When AI Sounds Too Certain",
          "subtitle": "Certainty that masks hidden uncertainty",
          "slidecontent": "• AI tools often state predictions in confident, authoritative language even when the underlying data is weak or incomplete\n• No caveats offered\n• A system might say \"sales will increase by 23%\" with no indication of how reliable that figure actually is\n• Confident phrasing can make guesswork sound like fact\n• Operators who trust these outputs without questioning them risk making critical decisions on shaky foundations\n• The problem is not the prediction itself, but the absence of any visible uncertainty around it"
