        {
          "number": 4,
          "slidetitle": "Recognising Overconfident AI Outputs",
          "subtitle": "Spotting the Signs Before It's Late",
          "slidecontent": "• AI outputs that express certainty without showing any margin of error or confidence range\n\n• Suspiciously round numbers\n\n• Predictions that align perfectly with what decision-makers hoped to hear\n\n• No acknowledgement of missing, incomplete, or low-quality input data\n\n• Consistent high confidence scores across very different types of questions\n\n• Language like \"will definitely\" or \"guaranteed outcome\" rather than \"likely\" or \"estimated\""
        },
