          "number": 5,
          "slidetitle": "Recognising the Warning Signs",
          "subtitle": "Spotting Overconfident AI Output Early",
          "slidecontent": "• AI outputs that include no uncertainty ranges or confidence intervals\n• Precise-sounding numbers (like \"87.3% probability\") with no supporting explanation\n• No caveats\n• Recommendations that ignore edge cases or conflicting data entirely\n• Language that presents one outcome as inevitable rather than likely\n• Consistent agreement with user assumptions, regardless of the input data"
